description:
RATFreqPrio: Table storing Radio Access Technology (RAT) frequency priorities for different cells, including time stamps, cell identifiers, and priority settings for various RATs (CDMA1xRtt, GERAN, EUTRA, UTRA, CDMA2000).
dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographic area.
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell site.
Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
Id3: An additional identifier (likely cell-specific).
Id4: An additional identifier (likely cell-specific, possibly related to rATFreqPrioId).
vsDataType: Data type identifier.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
RATFreqPrio.bandClassPrioListCDMA1xRtt: Priority list for CDMA1xRtt band classes.
RATFreqPrio.freqGroupPrioListGERAN: Priority list for GERAN frequency groups.
RATFreqPrio.userLabel: User-defined label.
RATFreqPrio.spidList: Service Provider ID list.
RATFreqPrio.ueCapPrioAllowed: Boolean indicating if UE capability priority is allowed.
RATFreqPrio.bandClassPrioListCDMA2000: Priority list for CDMA2000 band classes.
RATFreqPrio.t320: Timer value (likely related to handover).
RATFreqPrio.freqPrioListEUTRA: Priority list for EUTRA frequencies.
RATFreqPrio.freqPrioListUTRA: Priority list for UTRA frequencies.
RATFreqPrio.rATFreqPrioId: Unique identifier for the RAT frequency priority configuration.
